{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1037,"text":"Two twin domes,"},{"time":3708,"text":"two radically opposed design cultures."},{"time":7709,"text":"One is made of thousands of steel parts,"},{"time":10773,"text":"the other of a single silk thread."},{"time":14035,"text":"One is synthetic, the other organic."},{"time":16936,"text":"One is imposed on the environment,"},{"time":19237,"text":"the other creates it."},{"time":21666,"text":"One is designed for nature,\nthe other is designed by her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":26032,"text":"Michelangelo said that\nwhen he looked at raw marble,"},{"time":28949,"text":"he saw a figure struggling to be free."},{"time":31425,"text":"The chisel was Michelangelo's only tool."},{"time":37261,"text":"But living things are not chiseled."},{"time":39999,"text":"They grow."},{"time":41999,"text":"And in our smallest units of life,\nour cells, we carry all the information"},{"time":47489,"text":"that's required for every other cell\nto function and to replicate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54155,"text":"Tools also have consequences."},{"time":56922,"text":"At least since the Industrial Revolution,\nthe world of design has been dominated"},{"time":61556,"text":"by the rigors of manufacturing\nand mass production."},{"time":64703,"text":"Assembly lines have dictated\na world made of parts,"},{"time":67999,"text":"framing the imagination\nof designers and architects"},{"time":70615,"text":"who have been trained to think\nabout their objects as assemblies"},{"time":73743,"text":"of discrete parts with distinct functions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78165,"text":"But you don't find homogenous\nmaterial assemblies in nature."},{"time":83434,"text":"Take human skin, for example."},{"time":86054,"text":"Our facial skins are thin\nwith large pores."},{"time":89999,"text":"Our back skins are thicker,\nwith small pores."},{"time":93559,"text":"One acts mainly as filter,"},{"time":96201,"text":"the other mainly as barrier,"},{"time":97989,"text":"and yet it's the same skin:\nno parts, no assemblies."},{"time":102281,"text":"It's a system that gradually\nvaries its functionality"},{"time":105670,"text":"by varying elasticity."},{"time":107835,"text":"So here this is a split screen\nto represent my split world view,"},{"time":111801,"text":"the split personality of every designer\nand architect operating today"},{"time":116229,"text":"between the chisel and the gene,"},{"time":118572,"text":"between machine and organism,\nbetween assembly and growth,"},{"time":123434,"text":"between Henry Ford and Charles Darwin."},{"time":126734,"text":"These two worldviews,\nmy left brain and right brain,"},{"time":129760,"text":"analysis and synthesis, will play out\non the two screens behind me."},{"time":137754,"text":"My work, at its simplest level,"},{"time":140224,"text":"is about uniting these two worldviews,"},{"time":142983,"text":"moving away from assembly"},{"time":145221,"text":"and closer into growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149099,"text":"You're probably asking yourselves:"},{"time":151235,"text":"Why now?"},{"time":152766,"text":"Why was this not possible 10\nor even five years ago?"},{"time":158451,"text":"We live in a very special time in history,"},{"time":160603,"text":"a rare time,"},{"time":162699,"text":"a time when the confluence of four fields\nis giving designers access to tools"},{"time":167302,"text":"we've never had access to before."},{"time":170205,"text":"These fields are computational design,"},{"time":173093,"text":"allowing us to design\ncomplex forms with simple code;"},{"time":178125,"text":"additive manufacturing,\nletting us produce parts"},{"time":182183,"text":"by adding material\nrather than carving it out;"},{"time":185833,"text":"materials engineering, which lets us\ndesign the behavior of materials"},{"time":189301,"text":"in high resolution;"},{"time":191042,"text":"and synthetic biology,"},{"time":192923,"text":"enabling us to design new biological\nfunctionality by editing DNA."},{"time":197491,"text":"And at the intersection\nof these four fields,"},{"time":199755,"text":"my team and I create."},{"time":201492,"text":"Please meet the minds and hands"},{"time":203921,"text":"of my students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207772,"text":"We design objects and products\nand structures and tools across scales,"},{"time":213457,"text":"from the large-scale,"},{"time":215252,"text":"like this robotic arm\nwith an 80-foot diameter reach"},{"time":218792,"text":"with a vehicular base that will\none day soon print entire buildings,"},{"time":222950,"text":"to nanoscale graphics made entirely\nof genetically engineered microorganisms"},{"time":227061,"text":"that glow in the dark."},{"time":229261,"text":"Here we've reimagined the mashrabiya,"},{"time":231469,"text":"an archetype of ancient\nArabic architecture,"},{"time":234866,"text":"and created a screen where\nevery aperture is uniquely sized"},{"time":238454,"text":"to shape the form of light and heat\nmoving through it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242999,"text":"In our next project,"},{"time":244739,"text":"we explore the possibility\nof creating a cape and skirt --"},{"time":247973,"text":"this was for a Paris fashion show\nwith Iris van Herpen --"},{"time":251187,"text":"like a second skin\nthat are made of a single part,"},{"time":253999,"text":"stiff at the contours,\nflexible around the waist."},{"time":257589,"text":"Together with my long-term\n3D printing collaborator Stratasys,"},{"time":261813,"text":"we 3D-printed this cape and skirt\nwith no seams between the cells,"},{"time":266844,"text":"and I'll show more objects like it."},{"time":269452,"text":"This helmet combines\nstiff and soft materials"},{"time":272889,"text":"in 20-micron resolution."},{"time":276025,"text":"This is the resolution of a human hair."},{"time":278437,"text":"It's also the resolution of a CT scanner."},{"time":281531,"text":"That designers have access"},{"time":283096,"text":"to such high-resolution\nanalytic and synthetic tools,"},{"time":287518,"text":"enables to design products that fit\nnot only the shape of our bodies,"},{"time":292104,"text":"but also the physiological\nmakeup of our tissues."},{"time":296445,"text":"Next, we designed an acoustic chair,"},{"time":298477,"text":"a chair that would be at once\nstructural, comfortable"},{"time":301713,"text":"and would also absorb sound."},{"time":304529,"text":"Professor Carter, my collaborator, and I\nturned to nature for inspiration,"},{"time":308999,"text":"and by designing this irregular\nsurface pattern,"},{"time":311708,"text":"it becomes sound-absorbent."},{"time":314659,"text":"We printed its surface\nout of 44 different properties,"},{"time":318583,"text":"varying in rigidity, opacity and color,"},{"time":322000,"text":"corresponding to pressure points\non the human body."},{"time":326023,"text":"Its surface, as in nature,\nvaries its functionality"},{"time":330039,"text":"not by adding another material\nor another assembly,"},{"time":333690,"text":"but by continuously and delicately\nvarying material property."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340496,"text":"But is nature ideal?"},{"time":344146,"text":"Are there no parts in nature?"},{"time":349185,"text":"I wasn't raised\nin a religious Jewish home,"},{"time":352480,"text":"but when I was young,"},{"time":353660,"text":"my grandmother used to tell me\nstories from the Hebrew Bible,"},{"time":357081,"text":"and one of them stuck with me and came\nto define much of what I care about."},{"time":361110,"text":"As she recounts:"},{"time":363142,"text":"\"On the third day of Creation,\nGod commands the Earth"},{"time":366109,"text":"to grow a fruit-bearing fruit tree.\""},{"time":368649,"text":"For this first fruit tree,\nthere was to be no differentiation"},{"time":371900,"text":"between trunk, branches,\nleaves and fruit."},{"time":376294,"text":"The whole tree was a fruit."},{"time":380229,"text":"Instead, the land grew trees\nthat have bark and stems and flowers."},{"time":386337,"text":"The land created a world made of parts."},{"time":390514,"text":"I often ask myself,"},{"time":392396,"text":"\"What would design be like\nif objects were made of a single part?"},{"time":397412,"text":"Would we return to a better\nstate of creation?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":402999,"text":"So we looked for that biblical material,"},{"time":404978,"text":"that fruit-bearing fruit tree\nkind of material, and we found it."},{"time":411494,"text":"The second-most abundant biopolymer\non the planet is called chitin,"},{"time":415274,"text":"and some 100 million tons of it\nare produced every year"},{"time":418999,"text":"by organisms such as shrimps,\ncrabs, scorpions and butterflies."},{"time":423259,"text":"We thought if we could tune\nits properties,"},{"time":425999,"text":"we could generate structures\nthat are multifunctional"},{"time":428651,"text":"out of a single part."},{"time":430235,"text":"So that's what we did."},{"time":432999,"text":"We called Legal Seafood --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":435016,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":436076,"text":"we ordered a bunch of shrimp shells,"},{"time":438957,"text":"we grinded them\nand we produced chitosan paste."},{"time":442583,"text":"By varying chemical concentrations,"},{"time":444571,"text":"we were able to achieve\na wide array of properties --"},{"time":447889,"text":"from dark, stiff and opaque,"},{"time":449690,"text":"to light, soft and transparent."},{"time":452689,"text":"In order to print the structures\nin large scale,"},{"time":455653,"text":"we built a robotically controlled\nextrusion system with multiple nozzles."},{"time":460390,"text":"The robot would vary\nmaterial properties on the fly"},{"time":463572,"text":"and create these 12-foot-long structures\nmade of a single material,"},{"time":468699,"text":"100 percent recyclable."},{"time":471465,"text":"When the parts are ready,\nthey're left to dry"},{"time":474163,"text":"and find a form naturally\nupon contact with air."},{"time":478313,"text":"So why are we still\ndesigning with plastics?"},{"time":483999,"text":"The air bubbles that were a byproduct\nof the printing process"},{"time":487486,"text":"were used to contain\nphotosynthetic microorganisms"},{"time":490386,"text":"that first appeared on our planet\n3.5 billion year ago,"},{"time":493283,"text":"as we learned yesterday."},{"time":495999,"text":"Together with our collaborators\nat Harvard and MIT,"},{"time":498610,"text":"we embedded bacteria\nthat were genetically engineered"},{"time":501387,"text":"to rapidly capture carbon\nfrom the atmosphere"},{"time":504553,"text":"and convert it into sugar."},{"time":507449,"text":"For the first time,"},{"time":509260,"text":"we were able to generate structures\nthat would seamlessly transition"},{"time":513250,"text":"from beam to mesh,"},{"time":516608,"text":"and if scaled even larger, to windows."},{"time":520019,"text":"A fruit-bearing fruit tree."},{"time":522626,"text":"Working with an ancient material,"},{"time":525336,"text":"one of the first lifeforms on the planet,"},{"time":527999,"text":"plenty of water and a little bit\nof synthetic biology,"},{"time":531999,"text":"we were able to transform a structure\nmade of shrimp shells"},{"time":535530,"text":"into an architecture\nthat behaves like a tree."},{"time":539724,"text":"And here's the best part:"},{"time":542049,"text":"for objects designed to biodegrade,"},{"time":544020,"text":"put them in the sea,\nand they will nourish marine life;"},{"time":547740,"text":"place them in soil,\nand they will help grow a tree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552415,"text":"The setting for our next exploration\nusing the same design principles"},{"time":556456,"text":"was the solar system."},{"time":558693,"text":"We looked for the possibility\nof creating life-sustaining clothing"},{"time":562999,"text":"for interplanetary voyages."},{"time":566707,"text":"To do that, we needed to contain bacteria\nand be able to control their flow."},{"time":571769,"text":"So like the periodic table, we came up\nwith our own table of the elements:"},{"time":576353,"text":"new lifeforms that\nwere computationally grown,"},{"time":579766,"text":"additively manufactured"},{"time":581831,"text":"and biologically augmented."},{"time":586096,"text":"I like to think of synthetic biology\nas liquid alchemy,"},{"time":589645,"text":"only instead of transmuting\nprecious metals,"},{"time":592408,"text":"you're synthesizing new biological\nfunctionality inside very small channels."},{"time":596171,"text":"It's called microfluidics."},{"time":599067,"text":"We 3D-printed our own channels\nin order to control the flow"},{"time":603266,"text":"of these liquid bacterial cultures."},{"time":607432,"text":"In our first piece of clothing,\nwe combined two microorganisms."},{"time":611457,"text":"The first is cyanobacteria."},{"time":613392,"text":"It lives in our oceans\nand in freshwater ponds."},{"time":616392,"text":"And the second, E. coli, the bacterium\nthat inhabits the human gut."},{"time":620862,"text":"One converts light into sugar,\nthe other consumes that sugar"},{"time":624459,"text":"and produces biofuels\nuseful for the built environment."},{"time":627832,"text":"Now, these two microorganisms\nnever interact in nature."},{"time":632343,"text":"In fact, they never met each other."},{"time":634225,"text":"They've been here,\nengineered for the first time,"},{"time":637428,"text":"to have a relationship\ninside a piece of clothing."},{"time":641340,"text":"Think of it as evolution\nnot by natural selection,"},{"time":644999,"text":"but evolution by design."},{"time":647515,"text":"In order to contain these relationships,"},{"time":649738,"text":"we've created a single channel\nthat resembles the digestive tract,"},{"time":653867,"text":"that will help flow these bacteria\nand alter their function along the way."},{"time":658822,"text":"We then started growing\nthese channels on the human body,"},{"time":662475,"text":"varying material properties\naccording to the desired functionality."},{"time":665828,"text":"Where we wanted more photosynthesis,\nwe would design more transparent channels."},{"time":671101,"text":"This wearable digestive system,\nwhen it's stretched end to end,"},{"time":676229,"text":"spans 60 meters."},{"time":678317,"text":"This is half the length\nof a football field,"},{"time":680999,"text":"and 10 times as long\nas our small intestines."},{"time":685612,"text":"And here it is for the first time\nunveiled at TED --"},{"time":688344,"text":"our first photosynthetic wearable,"},{"time":690471,"text":"liquid channels glowing with life\ninside a wearable clothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694694,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":695846,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699871,"text":"Mary Shelley said, \"We are unfashioned\ncreatures, but only half made up.\""},{"time":703871,"text":"What if design could provide\nthat other half?"},{"time":707776,"text":"What if we could create structures\nthat would augment living matter?"},{"time":714035,"text":"What if we could create\npersonal microbiomes"},{"time":717492,"text":"that would scan our skins,\nrepair damaged tissue"},{"time":721391,"text":"and sustain our bodies?"},{"time":724062,"text":"Think of this as a form of edited biology."},{"time":726999,"text":"This entire collection, Wanderers,\nthat was named after planets,"},{"time":730999,"text":"was not to me really about fashion per se,"},{"time":733681,"text":"but it provided an opportunity\nto speculate about the future"},{"time":737064,"text":"of our race on our planet and beyond,"},{"time":739710,"text":"to combine scientific insight\nwith lots of mystery"},{"time":743465,"text":"and to move away\nfrom the age of the machine"},{"time":746810,"text":"to a new age of symbiosis\nbetween our bodies,"},{"time":750310,"text":"the microorganisms that we inhabit,"},{"time":752773,"text":"our products and even our buildings."},{"time":754725,"text":"I call this material ecology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757591,"text":"To do this, we always need\nto return back to nature."},{"time":762999,"text":"By now, you know that a 3D printer\nprints material in layers."},{"time":767759,"text":"You also know that nature doesn't."},{"time":770182,"text":"It grows. It adds with sophistication."},{"time":774102,"text":"This silkworm cocoon, for example,"},{"time":776690,"text":"creates a highly\nsophisticated architecture,"},{"time":780034,"text":"a home inside which to metamorphisize."},{"time":782859,"text":"No additive manufacturing today gets even\nclose to this level of sophistication."},{"time":788535,"text":"It does so by combining not two materials,"},{"time":791631,"text":"but two proteins\nin different concentrations."},{"time":795487,"text":"One acts as the structure,\nthe other is the glue, or the matrix,"},{"time":799507,"text":"holding those fibers together."},{"time":801952,"text":"And this happens across scales."},{"time":804717,"text":"The silkworm first attaches itself\nto the environment --"},{"time":807473,"text":"it creates a tensile structure --"},{"time":809513,"text":"and it then starts spinning\na compressive cocoon."},{"time":812999,"text":"Tension and compression,\nthe two forces of life,"},{"time":816554,"text":"manifested in a single material."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821337,"text":"In order to better understand\nhow this complex process works,"},{"time":824572,"text":"we glued a tiny earth magnet"},{"time":826783,"text":"to the head of a silkworm,\nto the spinneret."},{"time":829806,"text":"We placed it inside a box\nwith magnetic sensors,"},{"time":832778,"text":"and that allowed us to create\nthis 3-dimensional point cloud"},{"time":835889,"text":"and visualize the complex architecture\nof the silkworm cocoon."},{"time":841736,"text":"However, when we placed\nthe silkworm on a flat patch,"},{"time":845414,"text":"not inside a box,"},{"time":847176,"text":"we realized it would spin a flat cocoon"},{"time":850391,"text":"and it would still\nhealthily metamorphisize."},{"time":853781,"text":"So we started designing different\nenvironments, different scaffolds,"},{"time":857790,"text":"and we discovered that\nthe shape, the composition,"},{"time":860549,"text":"the structure of the cocoon, was directly\ninformed by the environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864866,"text":"Silkworms are often boiled to death\ninside their cocoons,"},{"time":869243,"text":"their silk unraveled and used\nin the textile industry."},{"time":872933,"text":"We realized that designing these templates\nallowed us to give shape to raw silk"},{"time":879416,"text":"without boiling a single cocoon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882950,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":886217,"text":"They would healthily metamorphisize,"},{"time":888963,"text":"and we would be able\nto create these things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891517,"text":"So we scaled this process up\nto architectural scale."},{"time":895170,"text":"We had a robot spin\nthe template out of silk,"},{"time":898325,"text":"and we placed it on our site."},{"time":900489,"text":"We knew silkworms migrated\ntoward darker and colder areas,"},{"time":905397,"text":"so we used a sun path diagram\nto reveal the distribution"},{"time":908741,"text":"of light and heat on our structure."},{"time":911692,"text":"We then created holes, or apertures,"},{"time":914226,"text":"that would lock in the rays\nof light and heat,"},{"time":917999,"text":"distributing those silkworms\non the structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":922777,"text":"We were ready to receive the caterpillars."},{"time":925174,"text":"We ordered 6,500 silkworms\nfrom an online silk farm."},{"time":930031,"text":"And after four weeks of feeding,\nthey were ready to spin with us."},{"time":933983,"text":"We placed them carefully\nat the bottom rim of the scaffold,"},{"time":937539,"text":"and as they spin they pupate,\nthey mate, they lay eggs,"},{"time":941999,"text":"and life begins all over again --\njust like us but much, much shorter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":948300,"text":"Bucky Fuller said that tension\nis the great integrity,"},{"time":953069,"text":"and he was right."},{"time":954716,"text":"As they spin biological silk\nover robotically spun silk,"},{"time":958462,"text":"they give this entire\npavilion its integrity."},{"time":961150,"text":"And over two to three weeks,"},{"time":963024,"text":"6,500 silkworms spin 6,500 kilometers."},{"time":967703,"text":"In a curious symmetry, this is also\nthe length of the Silk Road."},{"time":972837,"text":"The moths, after they hatch,\nproduce 1.5 million eggs."},{"time":976716,"text":"This could be used for 250\nadditional pavilions for the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":981639,"text":"So here they are, the two worldviews."},{"time":984728,"text":"One spins silk out of a robotic arm,"},{"time":988519,"text":"the other fills in the gaps."}]},{"cues":[{"time":992182,"text":"If the final frontier of design\nis to breathe life into the products"},{"time":995987,"text":"and the buildings around us,"},{"time":997805,"text":"to form a two-material ecology,"},{"time":999999,"text":"then designers must unite\nthese two worldviews."},{"time":1003627,"text":"Which brings us back, of course,\nto the beginning."},{"time":1008121,"text":"Here's to a new age of design,\na new age of creation,"},{"time":1011748,"text":"that takes us from\na nature-inspired design"},{"time":1015120,"text":"to a design-inspired nature,"},{"time":1017999,"text":"and that demands of us for the first time"},{"time":1021999,"text":"that we mother nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026793,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1027851,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034871,"text":"Thank you very much. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036999,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}